{"id": "EUVD-2022-55322", "enisaUuid": "2ce5ce73-be72-3b3b-b0be-da4379b6a9a3", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nASoC: SOF: debug: Fix potential buffer overflow by snprintf()\n\nsnprintf() returns the would-be-filled size when the string overflows\nthe given buffer size, hence using this value may result in the buffer\noverflow (although it's unrealistic).\n\nThis patch replaces with a safer version, scnprintf() for papering\nover such a potential issue.", "datePublished": "2025-06-18T12:30:44", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-13T21:31:18", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b318b9dd2ac67f39d0338ce563879d1f59a0347a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a67971a17604ae7de278fb09243432459afc51e1", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1eb123ce985e6cf302ac6e3f19862d132d86fa8f", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50051"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50051"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0ba9a2a3-d6cf-3fd3-b766-a1d69e2f6dd0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "5112da20-6ffb-343e-9ca0-17d0104ecde5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.63"}, {"id": "7779c9f8-1bfe-3226-be57-990fd7810796", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19.4"}, {"id": "931c3bed-f9d4-37b7-becc-a70831f88d4d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0"}, {"id": "941d8789-a750-38e3-9e3e-9024a16afdb9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5b10b62989219aa527ee4fa555d1995a3b70981b <b318b9dd2ac67f39d0338ce563879d1f59a0347a"}, {"id": "aaed4900-5062-3072-a996-d92080c3265b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5b10b62989219aa527ee4fa555d1995a3b70981b <1eb123ce985e6cf302ac6e3f19862d132d86fa8f"}, {"id": "b1ed6544-376b-30d1-afc1-283ca3b25200", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.11"}, {"id": "c1407712-b075-3335-bd17-b3ba81b02cbc", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_vers